    <h2 class="section-heading">Answer Writing Strategy</h2>

    <div class="syllabus-grid" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-5);">

      <div class="syl-card" style="--syl-color:#0f4c3a;">
        <div class="syl-card__head">
          <span class="syl-card__icon">📝</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="syl-card__title">10-Mark Answer (150 words)</h3>
            <span class="syl-card__count">~7-8 minutes</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:var(--space-4) var(--space-5); font-size:var(--text-sm); color:var(--color-text-secondary); line-height:var(--leading-relaxed);">
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Intro</strong> (1-2 lines) — Define concept or state context<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Body</strong> (8-10 lines) — 3-4 points with examples or data<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Conclusion</strong> (1-2 lines) — Way forward or balanced view
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="syl-card" style="--syl-color:#0f4c3a;">
        <div class="syl-card__head">
          <span class="syl-card__icon">📝</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="syl-card__title">15-Mark Answer (250 words)</h3>
            <span class="syl-card__count">~12-13 minutes</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:var(--space-4) var(--space-5); font-size:var(--text-sm); color:var(--color-text-secondary); line-height:var(--leading-relaxed);">
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Intro</strong> (2-3 lines) — Context + define the issue<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Body</strong> (15-18 lines) — Multi-dimensional: economic, social, political, environmental<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Diagram</strong> — Add one if relevant (saves words, scores marks)<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Conclusion</strong> (2-3 lines) — Balanced view + way forward
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="strategy-grid" style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Use Current Affairs</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Weave recent examples into every answer — committees, schemes, court judgments, international events. This separates average from top-scoring answers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Underline Keywords</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Examiners scan fast across 500+ answer sheets. Underline key terms, names, and data points. It draws the eye to your strongest content.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Never Skip a Question</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Write something for every question — even 3-4 points. An attempt with a basic structure scores 3-5 marks. A blank scores zero. That adds up.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Visual Clarity</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Start each point on a new line. Use headings and sub-points. Add simple diagrams or flowcharts. Presentation matters as much as content in Mains.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Time Discipline</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">20 questions in 3 hours = 9 minutes average. Budget 7 min for 10-markers, 13 min for 15-markers. Practice with a stopwatch. Speed comes from revision, not shortcuts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Directive Words</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">"Discuss" means cover all sides. "Critically examine" demands your conclusion. "Enumerate" means list with explanation. Misreading the directive loses marks on content you already know.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>
